%N A268602 Numerator of the side lengths (legs in ascending order) of the easiest Pythagorean Triangle (with smallest hypotenuse) according to the congruent numbers A003273.
%C A268602 Every three fractions x < y < z satisfy the Pythagorean equation x^2 + y^2 = z^2: (a(3*n-2)/A268603(3*n-2))^2 + (a(3*n-1)/A268603(3*n-1))^2 = (a(3*n)/A268603(3*n))^2.
%C A268602 The area A = x*y/2 of these Pythagorean triangles is a congruent number: A003273(n) = (1/2) * (a(3*n-2)/A268603(3*n-2)) * (a(3*n-1)/A268603(3*n-1)).
%H A268602 Editors of OEIS, <a href="/A268602/a268602.txt">Discussion of A268602</a>, Apr 22 2023.
%H A268602 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CongruentNumber.html">Congruent Number</a>.
%e A268602 The first congruent number is 5 and the associated right triangle with the side lengths x = 3/2, y = 20/3, z = 41/6 satisfies the Pythagorean equation (3/2)^2 + (20/3)^2 = (41/6)^2 and the area of this triangle equals 1/2*3/2*20/3 = 5.
